This paper deals with the design of optimal CRCs for convolutional codes, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves partitioning the tail-biting trellis and searching for irreducible error events, which are techniques commonly used in the design and analysis of discrete structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the properties of cyclic codes and the construction of tail-biting paths, which are topics related to coding theory (cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.CC).
